# error and accuracy
error:training error(empirical error) and generalization error

# the evalution method
hold-out:
(data set)D = S||T,S&T=MNULL
cross validation:
devide D data set into k sub dataset,called k fold cross validation
 LOO(leave one out):k=m
 bootstrapping:
 use the bootstrap sampling
 select a sample randomly from D to D' 
 parameter tuning:
 validation set: data set of evaluting the test  
 
# performance measure:
 compare the predicted answer to the truth ground 
 usally use mean squared error(MSE)
 error rate and accuracy:
 precision and recall:
  break even point(BEP):p(precision) = p(recall)
  F1 : the harmonic mean of the P,R,which care about the minest
 ROC and AUC
